text.section:
Any person who knowingly violates any of the provisions of KRS 121.035(2), 121.045, 121.055, 121.150 to 121.230, 121.310(1), or 121.320 shall, for each offense, be guilty of a Class D felony. Violations of KRS 121.150 to 121.230 shall include, but shall not be limited to, any of the following acts or omissions:
Failure to make required reports or to file reports at times specified;
Making any false statement or report;
Giving money under a fictitious name; or
Making any communication in violation of KRS 121.190(1).
